&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/science/domains/biology/domains/botany/terms/hosta/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/science/domains/biology/domains/botany/terms/hosta/> ;
  schema:name "Hosta" ;
  schema:description "Genus (~40 species) of perennial herbs from Asparagaceae, native to Japan, Korea, and China. Shade garden staples. Herbaceous rhizomatous perennials with broad, textured, variegated or solid-colored leaves arranged in basal mounds. Flowers are small, tubular to funnel-shaped, typically pale purple or white, produced on erect inflorescences (scapes). Hardy zones 3-9 depending on species/cultivar. Major threats: slugs, deer browsing. Formerly *Hosta* was classified within Liliaceae; molecular phylogenetics reclassified to Asparagaceae. Leaf shape, size, and color highly diverse across cultivars; variegation patterns are primary ornamental feature." ;
  schema:datePublished "2026-04-02" ;
  schema:dateModified "2026-04-02" ;
  schema:about &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/science/domains/biology/domains/botany/terms/hosta/> , &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/science/domains/biology/domains/botany/terms/hosta/> , &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/science/domains/biology/domains/botany/terms/hosta/> ;
